{
  "texts": [
    "Prompt-specific AES models are models that are trained and tested within the same domain.",
    "These models learn to capture the specific features of an essay topic based on a given prompt, enabling them to provide evaluations that are more specific to the domain.",
    "Such models are particularly useful in assessing essay quality traits such as prompt adherence and coherence.",
    "Prompt-specific holistic scoring AES models refer to AES models that are trained and tested within the same domain and predict an overall score.",
    "In this section, we explore various studies that focus on holistic scoring approaches."
  ]
}